# Spaced Repetition Schedule

Concepts move through intervals: 1 day → 3 days → 7 days → 14 days → 30 days.
A missed concept resets to the 1-day interval.

## Format

```
| Concept | Domain | Last Correct | Interval | Next Review |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Bell-LaPadula vs Biba | D3 | 2026-03-20 | 3 days | 2026-03-23 |
| ALE = SLE × ARO | D1 | 2026-03-18 | 7 days | 2026-03-25 |
| RPO vs RTO | D7 | 2026-03-25 | 1 day | 2026-03-26 |
```

## How This Works

- After each `/quiz` or `/rapid-fire` session, missed concepts are added at the 1-day interval
- Correctly answered concepts advance to the next interval
- The `/review` command reads this file and outputs a "due for review" list
- The exam skill reads this file to prioritize due concepts in question generation
